    "created_at": "2015-09-25T20:20:09Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-25T20:20:09Z",
    "body": "> You mention spawning a process as an example, but that's not the kind of API I had in mind when I said \"map directly to system APIs\" -- quite the opposite, since in Rust spawning involves quite a bit of work and several syscalls. I'm referring to APIs that map directly to a single (or in some cases two) system call.\n\nMy example was intended to be fictional, of course, and generally applies to a wide set of scenarios involving APIs that map to syscalls more directly. I only chosen `exec` as example, because it is my go to family of functions with a lot of them.\n",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
