    "created_at": "2015-10-22T19:46:20Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-22T19:46:20Z",
    "body": "How about a section of the `std::io` docs talking about \"Platform behavior\" sections which explains that the current documentation is roughly what happens under the hood but it's not guaranteed to stay the same over time? This could also take care of the boilerplate like CLOEXEC and non-inheritable handles on Windows. Each section could then look something along the lines of:\n\n```\n/// # Platform behavior\n///\n/// This function currently corresponds to the `open` function \n/// on Unix and the `CreateFile` function on Windows. Note that,\n/// this may [change in the future][link-here], however.\n```\n",
